The paper concerns randomized leader election in distributed networks, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithm presented in the paper involves message passing, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the mixing time of random walks on graphs, which is a topic in network science (cs.NE) and statistical physics (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DC and cs.DS, followed by cs.IT, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
